IV. WHAT HE WANTS FROM DAVINIA — THE PERSONAL AUDIENCE
=====================================================================
He will not take this secondhand from Orion. He needs her in person, and here is why:

- THE SUCCESSION STAKES: she is the one other living Caelus claim at his tier. A second
  genuine claimant is either his greatest threat (she could expose the inflation, or be
  raised against him by rivals) or his greatest instrument (a Caelus union would DOUBLE the
  legitimacy he is currently faking to Elisif). He decides which only by sitting across
  from her and taking her measure. That judgment is not delegable.
- THE NAG (GM-only, never spoken aloud, never confirmed to the players): something about
  her is off, and he cannot name it. He is an apex predator of stasis; she reads as older,
  stiller, and colder than a Breton woman should. He has no idea it's a Merethic-era queen
  wearing her. He just knows his instincts will not settle. Play the unease, NEVER the
  reveal — whether Ismara ever surfaces to him is entirely the player's call (Davinia's
  player drives Ismara; the GM only aims Valerius and gives roleplay pressure). He should
  leave the audience more unsettled than he arrived: the first being in centuries he
  cannot fully read.
- THE DANGER HE DOESN'T SEE: in courting or assessing a Caelus union, he is unknowingly
  negotiating with the very thing built to erase Davinia. If Ismara ever wants a throne
  again, Valerius just handed her a road into one. He will never realize this.

