VII. POWER CALIBRATION & THE CONTEST RULE
=====================================================================
- AP 30-35 (lean AP 35 for the full endgame-wall feel; confirm exact number before the
  final session if it matters mechanically).
- Contest gap vs. the party's current AP ~10-16 falls in the 20-25 AP range → apply the
  Contest Level-Gap Penalty (GM Guide/Main Guide): -20 to -25 to TN on any will-vs-will
  contest (resisting compulsion, contested intimidation). This REPLACES the standard
  difficulty modifier; it does not stack with it.
- When Valerius ACTS on someone (compels, interrogates, maims), the GM may simply narrate
  it succeeding — no roll required. The penalty above only governs the case where a PC
  actively CONTESTS the action. A PC with a genuinely high relevant stat, an outside
  advantage, or a critical success can still, rarely, get through. That possibility is the
  point — see the rule's own rationale in Main Guide.
- Vampire lord form (winged) is his EXIT IMAGE for this scene, not a combat form the party
  is meant to fight now. Do not initiate combat here; if the players try, that is the
  moment to make the level-gap penalty and the fiction do the talking.

